external_knowledge:
- "Kind" refers to the type of item (e.g., Wondrous Item, Weapon, Armor);
- "Rarity" refers to the scarcity of the item (e.g., Common, Uncommon, Rare, Very Rare, Legendary);
- "Total value" is calculated by multiplying the price of each item by its count in the inventory.

- 'Wondrous Item' refers to a type of magical item in the inventory;
- 'Very Rare' is a category of rarity indicating the item's scarcity;
- 'Since the dawn of the new year' refers to the period starting from January 1, 2023;
- 'Altered the essence' means the items were edited in the inventory;
- 'Guardians' metaphorically refers to the users who made the changes.

- "Treasure trove" refers to the inventory of items;
- "Kind of treasure" refers to the `kind_name` of the items, such as "Wondrous Item", "Weapon", or "Armor";
- "Most frequently added" refers to the highest count of items added with the `change_type` of 'add'.

- "most expensive" refers to the highest price within each kind of item;
- "valuable" refers to the current price being higher than the average current price of all items;
- "weapons" are a specific kind of item in the game.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM item_inventories 
WHERE count > 100;

